# iOS Accessibility Standards

These rules apply to all Habitat monorepo apps (Nuxt 4 SPA + Capacitor 8). They encode Apple HIG requirements and WCAG 2.2 Level AAA touch-target standards.

## Touch Targets

- **All** interactive elements (buttons, links, toggles, checkboxes, chips) must have a minimum touch area of **44×44px**.
- Use `min-h-[44px] min-w-[44px]`, the `.touch-target` utility, or the `.icon-btn` class.
- If the visual element is smaller (e.g., a 24px checkbox), expand the hit area with padding — the *tappable region* must still be 44×44.
- Exceptions: inline text links within paragraphs (exempt per WCAG 2.5.8).

## Accessible Labels

- **Every** icon-only button must have an `aria-label` describing its action (e.g., `aria-label="Delete habit"`).
- Never use `title` as the sole accessible name — it is not reliably announced by VoiceOver.
- Buttons with visible text do not need `aria-label` (the text *is* the label).
- Dynamic labels: include context (e.g., `` :aria-label="`Mark ${habit.name} complete`" ``).

## Semantic Elements

- Use `<button>` for actions, `<a>`/`<NuxtLink>` for navigation. Never use `<div @click>` for either.
- Use `role="button"` only on non-semantic elements that cannot be replaced with `<button>`.
- List items: `<ul>/<ol>` + `<li>`. If items are navigable, wrap content in `<a>`/`<NuxtLink>` inside the `<li>`.

## Segmented Controls and Toggles

- Container: `role="group"` + `aria-label="<group purpose>"`.
- Each segment: `aria-pressed="true|false"` (not `aria-selected` unless it's a tablist).
- Toggle switches: `role="switch"` + `aria-checked` + `aria-label`.

## Modals and Sheets

- Always: `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby`.
- Trap focus inside the modal while open.
- Return focus to the trigger element on close.

## Motion and Haptics

- Gate CSS animations with `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` and `html.reduce-motion`.
- Provide haptic feedback (`useHaptics`) on meaningful state changes: toggle, destructive confirm, navigation.
- Never use haptics for decorative/continuous animations.

## Testing

- Run `pnpm test:a11y` (axe-core + 44px audit) after any interactive element changes.
- Icon-only buttons without `aria-label` must fail lint/test — treat as a build error.
